WEBVTT

00:01.627 --> 00:02.913
<i>[eerie music]</i>

00:05.964 --> 00:07.830
<i>(male narrator) THERE
IS A FIFTH DIMENSION</i>

00:07.925 --> 00:10.292
<i>BEYOND THAT WHICH
IS KNOWN TO MAN.</i>

00:10.385 --> 00:13.343
<i>IT IS A DIMENSION
AS VAST AS SPACE</i>

00:13.430 --> 00:15.967
<i>AND AS TIMELESS
AS INFINITY.</i>

00:16.058 --> 00:20.017
<i>IT IS THE MIDDLE GROUND
BETWEEN LIGHT AND SHADOW</i>

00:20.103 --> 00:22.356
<i>BETWEEN SCIENCE
AND SUPERSTITION</i>

00:22.439 --> 00:25.602
<i>AND IT LIES BETWEEN
THE PIT OF MAN'S FEARS,</i>

00:25.692 --> 00:28.354
<i>AND THE SUMMIT
OF HIS KNOWLEDGE.</i>

00:28.445 --> 00:31.187
<i>THIS IS THE DIMENSION
OF IMAGINATION.</i>

00:31.281 --> 00:34.444
<i>IT I-S' A/VAREA VI/l-l/Cl-l
Vl/E CALL THE TVVILIGHT</i> ZONE.

00:41.291 --> 00:42.793
<i>[coin clinks]</i>

00:42.834 --> 00:44.290
<i>[someone dials
a phone]</i>

00:44.336 --> 00:46.452
<i>[sighs]</i>

00:51.134 --> 00:52.636
<i>[busy signal]</i>

00:55.847 --> 00:57.633
TELEPHONE--YOU
HAVE A TELEPHONE?

00:57.724 --> 00:59.465
THANK YOU.

00:59.560 --> 01:01.517
<i>[dialing again]</i>

01:04.313 --> 01:06.476
<i>[busy signal]</i>

01:06.525 --> 01:08.186
OH, THIS
IS MADNESS.

01:08.277 --> 01:10.484
IT'S IMPOSSIBLE TO MAKE
A CALL IN NEVV YORK.

01:10.571 --> 01:12.061
YOU CAN SAY
THAT AGAIN.

01:12.155 --> 01:14.021
THANK YOU.

01:14.116 --> 01:15.322
THIS IS
AN OUTRAGE!

01:15.409 --> 01:17.400
HE'S MAKING
ANOTHER CALL!

01:17.494 --> 01:19.155
IT'S ONLY
HIS FIFTH.

01:19.246 --> 01:20.657
HE DOESN'T
EVEN TALK.

01:20.706 --> 01:22.162
HE JUST DIALS.

01:22.249 --> 01:24.661
MAYBE HE'S GOT
A DIALECT, HUH?

01:26.461 --> 01:28.543
<i>(male narrator)
MR. ROGER SHACKLEFORTH--</i>

01:28.630 --> 01:30.371
<i>AGE, YOUTHFUL TWENTIES.</i>

01:30.465 --> 01:32.752
<i>OCCUPATION, BEING IN LOVE.</i>

01:32.843 --> 01:35.756
<i>NOT JUST IN LOVE,
BUT MADLY, PASSIONATELY</i>

01:35.846 --> 01:38.838
<i>ILLOGICALLY, MISERABLY,
ALL-CONSUMINGLY IN LOVE</i>

01:38.890 --> 01:40.722
<i>WITH A YOUNG WOMAN
NAMED LEILA</i>

01:40.809 --> 01:42.846
<i>WHO HAS A VAGUE
RECOLLECTION OF HIS FACE</i>

01:42.894 --> 01:45.932
<i>AND EVEN LESS
THAN A PASSING INTEREST.</i>

01:46.023 --> 01:47.684
<i>IN A MOMENT YOU'LL
SEE A SWITCH,</i>

01:47.774 --> 01:49.390
<i>BECAUSE MR. ROGER SHACKLEFORTH</i>

01:49.484 --> 01:51.316
<i>THE YOUNG GENTLEMAN
SO MUCH IN LOVE</i>

01:51.403 --> 01:54.441
<i>WILL TAKEA SHORT,
BUT VERY MEANINGFUL JOURNEY</i>

01:54.531 --> 01:55.987
<i>INTO THE TWILIGHT ZONE.</i>

02:04.374 --> 02:05.705
[busy signal]

02:05.792 --> 02:07.123
OH, I SIMPLY
CAN'T STAND THIS!

02:07.210 --> 02:08.951
I MUST GET
IN THERE NEXT.

02:09.045 --> 02:10.377
I WILL BUY YOUR PLACE.
A DOLLAR.

02:10.422 --> 02:11.878
OH! SOLD.

02:11.923 --> 02:13.209
THANK YOU.

02:13.300 --> 02:15.587
SIR. A DOLLAR
FOR YOUR PLACE.

02:15.677 --> 02:17.088
THANK YOU.

02:17.179 --> 02:18.920
MADAME. A DOLLAR FOR YOUR PLACE.

02:19.014 --> 02:21.722
VVHY SHOULD FIRST PLACE
BE THE SAME AS THE THIRD?

02:21.767 --> 02:23.098
TWO DOLLARS.

02:23.185 --> 02:25.802
TWO DOLLARS?
VERY GOOD.

02:25.896 --> 02:28.137
THERE YOU ARE.
THANK YOU.

02:31.401 --> 02:33.142
<i>[phone rings]</i>

02:37.074 --> 02:38.439
HELLO.

02:38.533 --> 02:41.150
HELLO, LEILA DARLING,
IT'S ROGER.

02:41.244 --> 02:43.576
OH.

02:43.622 --> 02:47.832
HELLO, ROGER.
[Sigh]

02:47.918 --> 02:49.033
WHAT IS IT?

02:49.127 --> 02:50.504
MAY I COME TO SEE YOU?

02:50.587 --> 02:52.999
UH, NO, NO, I CAN'T.

02:53.090 --> 02:54.751
I COULDN'T BEAR
TO SEE ANYBODY.

02:54.841 --> 02:56.172
I'M A MESS.

02:56.259 --> 02:58.421
OH, YOU COULD
NEVER BE A MESS.

02:58.470 --> 03:00.256
LISTEN, DARLING,
I HAVE TO SEE YOU.

03:00.347 --> 03:03.840
ROGER, IT'S IMPOSSIBLE.

03:03.934 --> 03:06.426
I MUST SEE YOU,
DARLING, MUST!

03:06.520 --> 03:09.638
FURIOUSLY, FIERCELY MUST!

03:09.731 --> 03:11.062
<i>[whispers]</i>
I <i>LOVE YOU.</i>

03:11.149 --> 03:13.811
ROGER, YOU'VE GOT
TO STOP THIS.

03:13.902 --> 03:15.939
YOU'RE ACTING
LIKE A BABY.

03:16.029 --> 03:18.270
I CAN'T SEE YOU NOW,
AND THAT'S THAT.

03:18.365 --> 03:19.696
WELL, THEN, TALK TO ME.

03:19.783 --> 03:21.524
SAY SOMETHING, SAY ANYTHING!

03:21.618 --> 03:27.034
SAY SOMETHING?

03:27.124 --> 03:30.537
ALL RIGHT, ROGER,
I'LL SAY SOMETHING.

03:30.627 --> 03:34.666
VVHY DON'T YOU TAKE A
FLYING JUMP AT THE MOON?

03:39.010 --> 03:41.217
THERE NOW, YOU'VE
FINISHED, HAVEN'T YOU?

03:41.304 --> 03:42.556
NO, SHE HUNG
UP ON ME.

03:42.639 --> 03:43.970
I'VE GOT
TO CALL HER BACK.

03:44.057 --> 03:45.297
NO, I HAVE
AN EMERGENCY.

03:45.350 --> 03:46.636
WELL, SO HAVE l.

03:46.727 --> 03:47.967
IT WON'T DO
ANY GOOD TO CALL.

03:48.061 --> 03:49.347
I UNDERSTAND
YOUR PROBLEM.

03:49.438 --> 03:50.974
I HEARD IT
THROUGH THE DOOR.

03:51.064 --> 03:52.805
<i>HERE'S THE WAY TO
SOLVE YOUR PROBLEM.</i>

03:52.858 --> 03:55.646
LOOK, GO AND SEE
THIS MAN RIGHT NOW.

03:55.694 --> 03:57.480
BELIEVE ME, THERE
IS NO OTHER WAY.

03:57.571 --> 03:58.777
THAT MAN WILL HELP YOU.

03:58.864 --> 04:00.275
NO--

04:00.365 --> 04:01.742
NO, EXCUSE ME.
GO AND SEE HIM NOW

04:01.825 --> 04:03.816
AND YOUR PROBLEMS
WILL BE SOLVED.

04:03.910 --> 04:05.651
THANK YOU,
THANK YOU.

04:05.746 --> 04:07.157
IT'S AN EMERGENCY!

04:07.247 --> 04:09.784
<i>[slams door]</i>

04:14.963 --> 04:16.464
<i>[loud bell rings]</i>

04:53.585 --> 04:55.201
ALL RIGHT,
ALL RIGHT.

04:55.295 --> 04:57.127
STOP SKULKING AROUND!

04:57.214 --> 04:58.545
L--l WASN'T SKULKING.

04:58.632 --> 05:00.122
I JUST DIDN'T
KNOW IF, UH--

05:00.217 --> 05:02.629
COMMON ENOUGH DISEASE,
NOT KNOWING IF.

05:02.719 --> 05:08.089
SIT DOWN ON THAT
PILE OF BOOKS THERE.

05:08.183 --> 05:09.218
DO I KNOW YOU?

05:09.309 --> 05:10.970
NO, SIR.

05:11.061 --> 05:12.972
AS A MATTER OF FACT--

05:13.063 --> 05:15.725
THEN YOU HAVEN'T COME FOR A
BOTTLE OF THE GLOVE CLEANER?

05:15.816 --> 05:18.148
GLOVE CLEANER?

05:18.235 --> 05:19.475
NO.

05:19.569 --> 05:20.821
AS A MATTER
OF FACT--

05:20.904 --> 05:24.067
WELL, PERHAPS
ANOTHER TIME.

05:24.157 --> 05:25.238
AS A MATTER
OF FACT...

05:25.325 --> 05:26.406
YOU KEEP SAYING THAT!

05:26.451 --> 05:27.987
COME TO THE POINT!

05:28.078 --> 05:29.989
<i>I DON'T KNOW
WHY I CAME AT ALL.</i>

05:30.080 --> 05:31.787
<i>YOU SEE, A MAN GAVE ME
YOUR CARD, A STRANGER.</i>

05:31.873 --> 05:35.116
OH, YES, SATISFIED FORMER
CUSTOMER, MOST LIKELY.

05:35.210 --> 05:36.666
BUT I DON'T KNOW
WHY I CAME.

05:36.753 --> 05:38.164
I WAS SITTING THERE--

05:38.255 --> 05:39.916
OF COURSE YOU KNOW
WHY YOU CAME!

05:40.006 --> 05:41.417
YOU WANT
WHAT I'VE GOT!

05:41.508 --> 05:43.215
BUT I DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU'VE GOT.

05:43.301 --> 05:47.966
OINTMENTS, SALVES,
POWDERS, SOVEREIGN REMEDIES,

05:48.056 --> 05:50.514
NECTARS, LOTUS BLOSSOMS,
TOXINS, TONICS,

05:50.600 --> 05:53.683
ANTI-TOXINS, DECOCTIONS,
CONCOCTIONS AND POTIONS--

05:53.770 --> 05:55.352
ALL GUARANTEED.

05:55.438 --> 05:57.816
OH.

05:57.899 --> 05:59.936
I DON'T NEED
ANYTHING LIKE THAT.

05:59.985 --> 06:01.817
WELL, YOU MUST,
YOU'RE HERE.

06:01.903 --> 06:04.144
YES, BUT I DON'T
NEED ANY MEDICINE.

06:04.239 --> 06:05.900
YOU CERTAINLY
NEED SOMETHING.

06:05.991 --> 06:07.777
YOU LOOK FEVERISH.

06:07.826 --> 06:12.036
OH, WELL, IT'S SORT
OF... YOU KNOW...

06:12.122 --> 06:14.113
NOTHING.

06:14.207 --> 06:15.948
"NOTHING" I
DON'T SUPPLY.

06:16.042 --> 06:17.624
"SOMETHING" IS
MY SPECIALTY.

06:17.711 --> 06:19.543
"ANYTHING" IS WHAT
YOU CAN GET HERE.

06:22.966 --> 06:26.004
YOU'RE AMBITIOUS,
IS THAT IT?

06:26.094 --> 06:28.461
YOU WANT SUCCESS,
MONEY, ADMIRERS,

06:28.513 --> 06:29.753
THE WORLD AT YOUR FEET.

06:29.848 --> 06:31.054
NO, THAT'S
NOT IT AT ALL.

06:31.141 --> 06:33.508
POWER! YOU WANT POWER.

06:33.602 --> 06:35.184
NO, YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND.

06:35.270 --> 06:37.728
ALL I WANT IS LEILA.

06:37.814 --> 06:38.895
LEILA?

06:38.982 --> 06:40.313
YES, IF I HAVE LEILA

06:40.400 --> 06:42.562
I CAN DO ALL
THE REST MYSELF.

06:42.652 --> 06:44.268
LEILA.

06:44.362 --> 06:45.523
I MIGHT HAVE KNOWN.

06:45.614 --> 06:47.150
ALL HE WANTS
IS LEILA.

06:47.240 --> 06:49.072
I OFFER HIM
PRACTICALLY ANYTHING

06:49.159 --> 06:50.490
AND ALL HE WANTS
IS LEILA.

06:50.577 --> 06:51.988
AND I GUESS
THERE'S NOTHING

06:52.037 --> 06:53.698
YOU CAN DO
ABOUT THAT!

06:53.788 --> 06:55.495
THAT'S THE SIMPLEST OF ALL--

06:55.540 --> 06:58.248
THE ELEMENTARY PARLOR
TRICK OF MY SCIENCE.

06:58.335 --> 06:59.541
YOU DISAPPOINT ME.

06:59.628 --> 07:02.086
NO, YOU
DON'T UNDERSTAND.

07:02.172 --> 07:03.662
YOU SEE,
I'M IN LOVE

07:03.757 --> 07:05.247
WITH SOMEBODY
NAMED LEILA

07:05.342 --> 07:07.754
BUT SHE'S NOT IN
LOVE WITH ME, AND...

07:07.844 --> 07:09.835
I DON'T KNOW WHY
I'M TELLING YOU THIS.

07:09.930 --> 07:12.888
I DO. I CAN ARRANGE IT
SO SHE'LL LOVE YOU.

07:12.974 --> 07:14.681
HOW?

07:14.726 --> 07:16.888
I PROMISE YOU

07:16.978 --> 07:18.935
SHE'LL NEVER LEAVE
YOUR SIDE.

07:19.022 --> 07:21.229
WHEN SHE ISN'T TELLING
YOU SHE LOVES YOU,

07:21.316 --> 07:23.899
SHE'LL BE GAZING
AT YOU LOVINGLY.

07:23.985 --> 07:25.896
SHE WON'T EVEN EAT
BEFORE YOU DO

07:25.987 --> 07:27.443
AND NOTHING
WILL BE TOO MUCH

07:27.530 --> 07:29.066
FOR YOU
TO ASK OF HER.

07:29.157 --> 07:31.194
SHE'LL WORSHIP YOU,
SHE'LL BEG FOR KISSES

07:31.284 --> 07:33.116
AND WEEP FOR JOY
AT YOUR TOUCH.

07:33.203 --> 07:34.739
AND IF IN PASSING TIME

07:34.829 --> 07:36.866
YOU SHOULD PERHAPS
LOOK AT ANOTHER GIRL

07:36.915 --> 07:39.452
OR EVEN DO A LITTLE
MORE THAN LOOK

07:39.542 --> 07:42.034
SHE'LL FEEL HURT,
BUT SHE'LL FORGIVE YOU

07:42.128 --> 07:43.960
AND LOVE YOU
JUST THE SAME.

07:44.047 --> 07:46.288
FRANKLY, YOU'D
GET THE SAME SHAKE

07:46.383 --> 07:47.623
FROM A COCKER SPANIEL.

07:47.717 --> 07:49.253
BUT THAT'S WONDERFUL!

07:49.344 --> 07:50.550
THAT'S <i>ALL</i> IN
THE WORLD I WANT--

07:50.595 --> 07:52.381
MY LEILA'S LOVE.

07:52.430 --> 07:54.137
HIS LEILA'S LOVE.

07:54.224 --> 07:56.215
IF IT ISN'T
HIS LEILA'S LOVE

07:56.267 --> 07:57.723
IT'S HIS DOROTHY'S LOVE,

07:57.811 --> 08:01.805
HIS RHEA'S LOVE,
OR HIS GWEN'S LOVE.

08:01.898 --> 08:04.390
TELL ME, ARE YOU SURE
YOU WOULDN'T BE INTERESTED

08:04.484 --> 08:06.395
IN THE GLOVE CLEANER,
AS I CALL IT?

08:06.486 --> 08:07.942
THERE ARE
MANY NAMES FOR IT

08:08.029 --> 08:12.068
INCLUDING "THE ERADICATOR."

08:12.158 --> 08:13.569
BUT "GLOVE CLEANER"

08:13.660 --> 08:16.493
IS A NICE,
NONDESCRIPTIVE TITLE.

08:16.579 --> 08:18.570
CLEAN, COLORLESS, TASTELESS

08:18.665 --> 08:20.155
UNIDENTIFIABLE AND SURE.

08:20.250 --> 08:23.333
I'M NOT INTERESTED
IN GLOVE CLEANERS.

08:23.420 --> 08:25.002
WHY NOT?

08:25.088 --> 08:27.329
IT'S SURE, IT'S SWIFT,
LEAVES NO TRACES.

08:27.424 --> 08:30.007
IT'S PERFECT
FOR ITS PURPOSE.

08:30.093 --> 08:32.424
I DON'T THINK YOU'RE
MAKING ANY SENSE.

08:32.511 --> 08:34.594
MY BOY,
THAT'S ALL I MAKE.

08:34.681 --> 08:38.424
WHICH IS WHY I'M
SUCH A LONELY MAN.

08:38.518 --> 08:40.350
YOU'RE SURE YOU
DON'T WANT TO TRY

08:40.437 --> 08:41.677
THE GLOVE CLEANER?

08:41.770 --> 08:43.352
IT'S VERY EXPENSIVE.

08:43.440 --> 08:45.101
PERHAPS YOU
CAN'T AFFORD IT.

08:45.191 --> 08:48.934
FOR INSTANCE THIS LITTLE
BOTTLE COSTS $1 ,OOO.

08:49.029 --> 08:51.612
$1,000? ARE ALL YOUR
PRICES LIKE THAT?

08:51.656 --> 08:53.112
SOME ARE,
SOME AREN'T.

08:53.158 --> 08:54.569
YEAH, BUT
THAT THING

08:54.617 --> 08:56.278
THAT'S GONNA
MAKE LEILA LOVE ME.

08:56.369 --> 08:58.531
OH, THAT.

08:58.621 --> 09:00.874
THAT'S ONLY
A DOLLAR.

09:00.957 --> 09:04.200
A DOLLAR?

09:04.294 --> 09:07.002
LOVE POTIONS ARE
MY CHEAPEST ITEM.

09:07.088 --> 09:09.170
AND THEY'RE
OVERPRICED AT THAT.

09:09.257 --> 09:11.715
A DOLLAR FOR
MY LEILA'S LOVE?

09:11.801 --> 09:13.883
IT WON'T HURT HER?

09:13.970 --> 09:16.837
IF ANYBODY GETS HURT,
IT'LL BE YOU.

09:16.931 --> 09:21.846
BUT I DON'T EXPECT
YOU TO BELIEVE ME.

09:21.936 --> 09:23.643
PUT IT IN ANYTHING--

09:23.730 --> 09:26.267
HER DRINK, JUICE, SOUP,
COFFEE, WATER, ANYTHING.

09:26.357 --> 09:28.689
YOU'LL GET EXACTLY
WHAT YOU SAY YOU WANT.

09:28.777 --> 09:31.360
VVELL, I DON'T REALLY BELIEVE
THIS BUT I'LL TRY IT.

09:31.446 --> 09:33.062
WHY, I'LL TRY ANYTHING.

09:33.156 --> 09:34.692
THANKS, PROFESSOR.

09:34.783 --> 09:36.490
YOU KNOW, IF THIS
WORKS, I'LL BE--

09:36.576 --> 09:39.989
(both) THE HAPPIEST
MAN IN THE WORLD.

09:40.080 --> 09:43.243
<i>[doorbell buzzes]</i>

09:50.590 --> 09:52.251
HELLO, LEILA.

09:52.342 --> 09:55.676
ROGER, I TOLD YOU
I WAS BUSY TONIGHT.

09:55.720 --> 09:58.098
WELL, JUST A MINUTE,
JUST A LITTLE MINUTE.

09:58.181 --> 10:00.923
FLOWERS, SEE?

10:01.017 --> 10:03.008
THAT'S VERY NICE,
ROGER, THANK YOU.

10:03.061 --> 10:04.472
NOW IF YOU'LL
JUST RUN ALONG.

10:04.562 --> 10:06.018
I COULDN'T HAVE
LASTED THE EVENING

10:06.106 --> 10:07.767
WITHOUT SEEING
YOU, LEILA.

10:07.857 --> 10:10.064
YOU DON'T KNOW WHAT IT'S
LIKE TO LOVE SOMEBODY

10:10.151 --> 10:12.859
TO LOVE ANYBODY SO MUCH
AND SO DESPERATELY.

10:12.946 --> 10:15.859
LOOK, CHAMPAGNE--

10:15.949 --> 10:17.360
JUST ENOUGH
FOR TWO GLASSES.

10:17.450 --> 10:18.690
THAT'S NOT
ASKING MUCH.

10:18.785 --> 10:20.071
JUST SPARE ME
FIVE MINUTES

10:20.161 --> 10:21.617
AND HAVE ONE
DRINK WITH ME.

10:21.704 --> 10:25.447
ROGER, YOU ARE
ACTING LIKE A CLOD--

10:25.542 --> 10:28.751
A SILLY, STUPID,
SOPHOMORIC CLOD.

10:28.837 --> 10:30.748
I LOVE YOU.

10:30.839 --> 10:33.501
STOP SAYING THAT. I--

10:38.179 --> 10:40.136
ALL RIGHT.

10:40.223 --> 10:42.214
ONE DRINK.

10:42.267 --> 10:45.430
FIVE MINUTES,
AND THEN YOU GO.

10:50.066 --> 10:53.229
I'VE GOT TO PUT
ON MY DRESS.

10:57.240 --> 11:00.483
IT'S LIKE...

11:00.577 --> 11:02.067
IT'S LIKE MILLENNIUM.

11:33.651 --> 11:36.234
WELL, LET'S GET
THIS OVER WITH.

11:54.172 --> 11:55.788
WELL, YOUR TIME'S UP.

11:55.882 --> 11:57.293
THANK YOU VERY MUCH

11:57.383 --> 12:00.045
FOR THE FLOWERS
AND THE CHAMPAGNE.

12:00.136 --> 12:02.969
NOW, GOODBYE, ROGER.

12:07.352 --> 12:10.310
EXCELLENT CHAMPAGNE,
WASN'T IT?

12:10.396 --> 12:12.057
IT'LL PASS.

12:12.148 --> 12:14.059
VVHAT ARE YOU LOOKING
AT ME LIKE THAT FOR?

12:14.150 --> 12:17.984
WELL, PERHAPS
IT'S MY LAST LOOK.

12:18.029 --> 12:22.398
ALL RIGHT,
YOU'VE HAD IT.

12:22.492 --> 12:24.324
ONE LAST
LITTLE KISS?

12:24.410 --> 12:27.994
ROGER, PLEASE, LET'S NOT
PROLONG THIS ANY LONGER.

12:28.081 --> 12:29.492
I HAVEN'T THE TIME.

12:29.582 --> 12:30.572
NOW PLEASE GO.

12:30.667 --> 12:33.250
NOW!

12:33.336 --> 12:35.748
I DON'T LOVE YOU.

12:35.838 --> 12:37.875
I DON'T WANT YOU HERE.

12:37.966 --> 12:39.877
I DON'T EVEN LIKE
YOU AT THE MOMENT.

12:39.968 --> 12:41.834
NOW PLEASE GO!

12:46.516 --> 12:50.054
OH!

12:50.144 --> 12:51.521
HERE.

12:54.816 --> 12:57.899
THAT'S THE BEST
I CAN DO.

12:57.986 --> 13:00.068
AND THAT TOOK
ALL MY STRENGTH.

13:04.492 --> 13:06.358
ROGER...

13:06.452 --> 13:10.787
WAIT A MINUTE.

13:10.873 --> 13:13.740
PERHAPS I AM
BEING CRUEL.

13:13.835 --> 13:16.543
I DON'T MEAN TO BE.

13:16.629 --> 13:20.247
I KNOW.

13:20.341 --> 13:21.376
ROGER!

13:26.681 --> 13:31.141
LET ME--MAKE IT
A LITTLE NICER.

13:40.737 --> 13:43.149
WHAT'S HAPPENING?

13:43.239 --> 13:44.946
WHAT'S HAPPENING?

13:45.033 --> 13:46.615
WHAT DIFFERENCE?

13:46.701 --> 13:48.237
COME HERE, BABY.

13:48.286 --> 13:49.697
[shrieks]

14:06.929 --> 14:09.466
LEILA, COULDN'T YOU
PLEASE SIT IN A CHAIR?

14:09.557 --> 14:12.515
OH, YES, MY
DARLING HUSBAND.

14:12.602 --> 14:15.094
OH, I'M SORRY
IF IT BOTHERS YOU,

14:15.146 --> 14:19.936
IT'S JUST THAT I LOVE
TO KNEEL AT YOUR FEET.

14:20.026 --> 14:21.437
